-- Xerox to buy Global Imaging Systems for $1.5 bln
-- 
-- Mon Apr 2, 2007 6:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/02/us-xerox-takeover-globalimaging-idUSWNAS535220070402

 

 (Reuters) - Xerox Corp. ( XRX.N ) said it agreed to acquire office technology products provider Global Imaging Systems Inc. GISX.O for about $1.5 billion. 

 The deal valued at $29 a share represents a near 50 percent premium to Global Imaging stock's Friday closing price. Xerox expects the acquisition of Global to be accretive to Xerox's full-year 2007 earnings. (Reporting by Ankur Relia in Bangalore)